---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { url } from '../utils/url';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Ashish Mehta" description="Ashish Mehta — engineer at Hippocratic AI. Writes about LLM RL systems, distributed ML infrastructure, and the things in between.">
  <article class="about prose">
    <header class="about-hero">
      <div class="about-hero-photo">
        <!-- Replace with a real headshot at /headshot.jpg -->
        <img src={url('headshot.jpg')} alt="Ashish Mehta" onerror="this.style.visibility='hidden'" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-hero-text">
        <h1>Ashish Mehta</h1>
        <p class="about-role">Engineer · Hippocratic AI</p>
        <p class="about-tagline">
          I work on reinforcement learning systems for large language models — the
          infrastructure that turns "you have a base model and a reward signal" into
          "you have a fine-tuned model that actually does the thing."
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>About this site</h2>
      <p>
        This is where I write long-form notes on the systems I work with. The headline
        piece right now is <a href={url('series/llm-rl-systems/')}>A systems view of LLM RL</a>,
        a 12-post systems study — orchestration, the algorithm interface, reward design,
        the multi-turn agent machinery, the engine split, scaling, observability, a
        cross-framework comparison, a design-patterns synthesis, an open-problems agenda,
        and field notes from production runs — with VERL as the worked example. The series is
        meant for RL practitioners who want the systems context and for systems
        engineers who want the RL context.
      </p>
      <p>
        I publish what I write as I learn it. The posts are detailed because the
        questions are detailed; the visualizations are interactive because the
        systems are interactive.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Selected work</h2>
      <ul class="about-list">
        <li>
          <strong><a href={url('series/llm-rl-systems/')}>A systems view of LLM RL</a></strong>
          (2026) — 12-post technical series on LLM RL systems, including
          first-hand field notes from production RL runs. Tens of thousands
          of words, 40+ hand-authored interactive visualizations.
        </li>
        <li>
          <em>(More entries will land here as the body of work grows. If you want
          something specific surfaced — papers, talks, projects — message me.)</em>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Find me</h2>
      <ul class="about-list about-links">
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:ashish@hippocraticai.com">ashish@hippocraticai.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/AshishMehtaIO" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@AshishMehtaIO</a></li>
        <li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ashishmehtaio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">in/ashishmehtaio</a></li>
        <li><strong>Google Scholar:</strong> <a href="https://scholar.google.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">profile</a> <em class="about-hint">(link to be updated)</em></li>
        <li><strong>RSS:</strong> <a href={url('rss.xml')}>{url('rss.xml')}</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-cite">
      <h2>Citing this work</h2>
      <p>
        If you reference posts from this site in academic or professional work, here is a
        citation template:
      </p>
      <pre class="about-bibtex">{`@misc{mehta2026llmrl,
  author       = {Ashish Mehta},
  title        = {A systems view of LLM RL},
  year         = {2026},
  url          = {https://ashishmehtaio.github.io/ashish-ai-blog/series/llm-rl-systems/},
  note         = {Online; published as a series of blog posts}
}`}</pre>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: var(--content-width-wide);
    margin: 5rem auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr;
    gap: 1.75rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; text-align: center; }
    .about-hero-photo { justify-self: center; }
  }

  .about-hero-photo {
    width: 140px;
    height: 140px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
  }
  .about-hero-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .about-hero-text h1 {
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.5rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .about-role {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .about-tagline {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  section {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }
  section h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }

  .about-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .about-list li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .about-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .about-links li strong {
    display: inline-block;
    min-width: 120px;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .about-hint {
    color: var(--text-faint);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-left: 0.35rem;
  }

  .about-cite {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }
  .about-cite h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  .about-bibtex {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }
</style>
